   <div class="container">
    <div class="welcome_message_content">
     <h1 class="pg-hdr">
      Welcome
     </h1>
     <p>
      The University of Chicago's emeriti faculty have raised the bar for research and teaching throughout their distinguished academic careers. Their research has driven and continues to drive fields of inquiry, and they have modeled Chicago philosophy, integrity, and critical thought for countless students. There are diverse ways emeriti engage in the University community after retirement—whether through continuing scholarship and teaching, providing input, or simply staying up–to–date on campus developments, emeriti are an important part of the University of Chicago.
     </p>
     <p>
      This website has been developed to provide information and links to emeriti resources, which are updated ongoingly. Some useful direct links included here will take you to: the
      <a href="https://emeritifaculty.uchicago.edu/resources/robert-and-anne-gomer-lecture-series">
       Gomer lecture recordings
      </a>
      ,
      <a href="https://emeritifaculty.uchicago.edu/resources/transportation">
       transportation information
      </a>
      , and the
      <a href="https://emeritifaculty.uchicago.edu/emeriti-updates">
       Emeriti Update
      </a>
      s page.
     </p>
     <p>
      Please reach out to us with any suggestions, questions, or other feedback.
     </p>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container">
   <div class="row">
    <div class="news_feature">
     <h2 class="pg-hdr">
      Announcements
     </h2>
     <h3>
      <a href="https://emeritifaculty.uchicago.edu/news-announcements/article/conference-in-honor-of-the-late-prof.-emeritus-heshmat-moayyad-march-8-9-20">
       Conference in honor of the late Prof. Emeritus Heshmat Moayyad, March 8-9, 2019
      </a>
     </h3>
     <img alt="{alt_text}" class="lazy people_photo" src="https://d3qi0qp55mx5f5.cloudfront.net/emeritifaculty/i/news/Heshmat_Moayyad.jpg?mtime=1530893277"/>
     <p>
      The Center for Middle Eastern Studies is hosting a conference on Persian and Iranian Studies in honor of the late Professor Emeritus Heshmat Moayyad. The conference will be on March 8-9, 2019, at the Franke Institute.
     </p>
     <a class="readmore" href="https://emeritifaculty.uchicago.edu/news-announcements/article/conference-in-honor-of-the-late-prof.-emeritus-heshmat-moayyad-march-8-9-20">
      Read More
     </a>
    </div>
    <div class="news">
     <h2 class="pg-hdr">
      News
     </h2>
     <ul class="news_feed">
      <li>
       <h3>
        <a href="https://emeritifaculty.uchicago.edu/news-announcements/article/prof.-emerita-sheila-fitzpatrick-to-be-a-neubauer-collegium-visiting-fellow">
         Prof. Emerita Sheila Fitzpatrick to be a Neubauer Collegium visiting fellow, fall 2020
        </a>
       </h3>
       <p>
        Sheila Fitzpatrick, the Bernadotte E. Schmitt Distinguished Service Professor Emerita of Russian History and the College, will be participating in the Revolutionology project at the Neubauer Collegium in fall 2020.
       </p>
      </li>
      <li>
       <h3>
        <a href="https://emeritifaculty.uchicago.edu/news-announcements/article/john-e-frederick-1949-2019">
         John E. Frederick, Prof. Emeritus of atmospheric science and Quantrell Award winner, 1949-2019
        </a>
       </h3>
       <p>
        John Eugene Frederick, Professor Emeritus in the Department of the Geophysical Sciences, passed away unexpectedly on January 30, 2019. He was 69.
       </p>
      </li>
      <li>
       <h3>
        <a href="https://emeritifaculty.uchicago.edu/news-announcements/article/eric-hamp-1920-2019">
         Eric Hamp, Prof. Emeritus and leading authority on Indo-European languages, 1920-2019
        </a>
       </h3>
       <p>
        Eric Hamp, the Robert Maynard Hutchins Distinguished Service Professor Emeritus in the Departments of Linguistics, Slavic Languages and Literatures, Psychology, and the Committee on the Ancient Mediterranean World, passed away February 17, 2019. He was 98.
       </p>
      </li>
     </ul>
    </div>
